				<p><p>You are using one PID controller to try to drive a quaternion? A quaternion by definition represents three degrees of freedom, roll pitch yaw, and a PID controller is Single Input, Single Output (SISO) controller. </p>

<p>You're trying to mask a Multiple Input, Multiple Output (MIMO) system by hiding your three variables in a quaternion. </p>

<p>I would suggest maybe you consider using three PID controllers. If you're concerned about singularities, try going for an axis-angle configuration, where two controllers drive the azimuth and elevation of the axis and a third drives the rotation.</p>
</p><br>
